      • getRankingsForEncounter

        EncounterRankings getRankingsForEncounter(int encounterID,
                                          RankingMetric metric,
                                          java.lang.Integer size,
                                          EncounterDifficulty difficulty,
                                          EncounterRegion region,
                                          java.lang.Integer classID,
                                          java.lang.Integer specID,
                                          java.lang.Integer bracket,
                                          java.lang.Integer limit,
                                          java.lang.Integer page)
        Gets an object that contains a total count and an array of EncounterRanking objects and a total number of rankings for that encounter. Each EncounterRanking corresponds to a single character or guild/team
        Parameters:
        encounterID - The encounter to collect rankings for. Encounter IDs can be obtained using a /zones request.
        metric - The metric to query for. Valid fight metrics are 'speed', 'execution' and 'feats'. Valid character metrics are 'dps', 'hps', 'bossdps, 'tankhps', or 'playerspeed'. For WoW only, 'krsi' can be used for tank survivability ranks.
        size - The raid size to query for. This is only valid for fixed size raids. Raids with flexible sizing must omit this parameter.
        difficulty - The difficulty setting to query for. Valid difficulty settings are 1 = LFR, 2 = Flex, 3 = Normal, 4 = Heroic, 5 = Mythic, 10 = Challenge Mode, 100 = WildStar. Can be omitted for encounters with only one difficulty setting.
        region - The region group to query for. Valid options are 1 for US/EU and 2 for Asia. If omitted, US/EU is assumed.
        classID - The class to query for if a character metric is specified. Valid class IDs can be obtained from a /classes API request. Optional.
        specID - The spec to query for if a character metric is specified. Valid spec IDs can be obtained from a /classes API request. Optional.
        bracket - The bracket to query for. If omitted or if a value of 0 is specified, then all brackets are examined. Brackets can be obtained from a /zones API request.
        limit - The number of results to return at a time. If omitted, a default of 200 is assumed. Values greater than 5000 are not allowed.
        page - The page to examine, starting from 1. If the value is omitted, then 1 is assumed. For example, with a page of 2 and a limit of 300, you will be fetching rankings 301-600.
        Returns:
        EncounterRankings for the given encounter.

      • getRankingsForCharacter

        java.util.List<CharacterRanking> getRankingsForCharacter(java.lang.String characterName,
                                                         WarcraftServer serverName,
                                                         ServerRegion region,
                                                         java.lang.String zone,
                                                         RankingMetric metric,
                                                         java.lang.Integer bracket,
                                                         java.lang.Integer limit)
        Gets an array of CharacterRanking objects. Each CharacterRanking corresponds to a single rank on a fight for the specified character.
        Parameters:
        characterName - The name of the character to collect rankings for.
        serverName - The server that the character is found on. For World of Warcraft this is the 'slug' field returned from their realm status API.
        region - The short region name for the server on which the character is located: US, EU, KR, TW, CN.
        zone - The zone to fetch rankings for. If omitted, the latest open raid zone is used. This is currently Highmaul for WoW and Datascape for WildStar.
        metric - The metric to query for. Valid character metrics are 'dps', 'hps', 'bossdps, 'tankhps', or 'playerspeed'. For WoW only, 'krsi' can be used for tank survivability ranks.
        bracket - The bracket to query for. If omitted or if a value of 0 is specified, then all brackets are examined. Brackets can be obtained from a /zones API request.
        limit - The cutoff beyond which ranks will not be checked. The character only ranks if they are within the limit. The default value is 200, and the maximum allowed value is 5000.
        Returns:
        List of character rankings

      • getReportsForGuild

        java.util.List<Report> getReportsForGuild(java.lang.String guildName,
                                          WarcraftServer server,
                                          ServerRegion region,
                                          java.lang.Long start,
                                          java.lang.Long end)
        Gets an array of Report objects. Each Report corresponds to a single calendar report for the specified guild.
        Parameters:
        guildName - The name of the guild to collect reports for.
        server - The server that the guild is found on. For World of Warcraft this is the 'slug' field returned from their realm status API.
        region - The short region name for the server on which the guild is located: US, EU, KR, TW, CN.
        start - An optional start time. This is a UNIX timestamp but with millisecond precision. If omitted, 0 is assumed.
        end - An optional end time. This is a UNIX timestamp but with millisecond precision. If omitted, the current time is assumed.
        Returns:
        An list of Report objects for the given guild.
